The article discusses an Executive Order signed by the President to improve the safety and security of chemical facilities and reduce the risks of hazardous chemicals to workers and communities. The order focuses on four key areas: improving operational coordination with state and local partners, enhancing federal agency coordination and information sharing, modernizing policies, regulations, and standards, and working with stakeholders to identify best practices. It highlights the importance of federal agencies working together to address risks associated with chemical facilities and emphasizes the need for improved coordination and information sharing with state and local governments. The article also provides an overview of existing federal programs aimed at addressing chemical safety and security at chemical facilities.